.SH "NAME"
dentry_update_name_case \- update case insensitive dentry with a new name
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'void\ dentry_update_name_case('u
.BI "void dentry_update_name_case(struct\ dentry\ *\ " "dentry" ", const\ struct\ qstr\ *\ " "name" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIdentry\fR
.RS 4
dentry to be updated
.RE
.PP
\fIname\fR
.RS 4
new name
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Update a case insensitive dentry with new case of name\&.
.PP
dentry must have been returned by d_lookup with name
\fIname\fR\&. Old and new name lengths must match (ie\&. no d_compare which allows mismatched name lengths)\&.
.PP
Parent inode i_mutex must be held over d_lookup and into this call (to keep renames and concurrent inserts, and readdir(2) away)\&.
